#!/bin/bash
genomefa_dir="/data1/project/omics_final"
Q1_dir="/data1/project/omics_final/Q1"
genomes=(T2T GRCh38_p14)
mer_lens=($(seq 2 20))

mkdir -p ${Q1_dir}
for genome in ${genomes[@]};do 

    for i in ${mer_lens[@]};do
        # 1 k-mer
        jellyfish count -m ${i} \
            -s 3G \
            -t 20 \ 
            -o ${Q1_dir}/${genome}_${i}.jf \
             ${genomefa_dir}/${genome}.fa 
    done
done

#!/bin/bash
Q1_dir="/data1/project/omics_final/Q1"

for jf in ${Q1_dir}/*.jf;do 

    prefix=$(basename ${jf} .jf)
    
    jellyfish dump ${jf} > ${Q1_dir}/${prefix}.txt # k-merhttps://github.com/gmarcais/Jellyfish/tree/master/doc#dump
    jellyfish histo ${jf} > ${Q1_dir}/${prefix}.histo # k-merhttps://github.com/gmarcais/Jellyfish/tree/master/doc#histo
    jellyfish stats ${jf} > ${Q1_dir}/${prefix}.stats # 

done

import pandas as pd
import argparse

def calculate_enrichment_score(kmer_file,total_obs_count,exp_freq_dict_type,top_m=10):
    """
    Args:
        kmer_file (str): k-mer
        total_obs_count (int): top k-mer
        shellcut -d " " -f 2 k-mer | awk '{sum+=$1} END {print sum}'
        exp_freq_dict_type (str):"grch38_p14""t2t"GRCh38_p14T2T
        1exp_freq_dict (dict): 
        top_m (int): top_mk-mer,10

    Fun:
         =  / 
         = k-mer / 
        
        k-mertop_m
    """
    top_kmer = pd.read_csv(kmer_file,sep=" ",header=None,names=["kmer","count"])

    # 
    top_kmer["obs_freq"] = top_kmer["count"] / total_obs_count

    # 
    # k-merk-merfor i in top_kmer["kmer"]
    grch38_p14_freq = {"A": 0.2942844830001953, "C": 0.20484219378112098, "G": 0.20569626883883788, "T": 0.2951770543798458}
    t2t_freq = {"A": 0.2963722334173198, "C": 0.20328436340583256, "G": 0.20425501675882426, "T": 0.2960883864180234}
    if exp_freq_dict_type == "grch38_p14":
        exp_freq_dict = grch38_p14_freq
    elif exp_freq_dict_type == "t2t":
        exp_freq_dict = t2t_freq
    else:
        raise ValueError("exp_freq_dict_type must be 'grch38_p14' or 't2t'")

    def calc_exp_freq(kmer,exp_freq_dict):
        freq = 1.0
        for base in kmer:
            freq *= exp_freq_dict.get(base,0) # 0
        return freq
    
    top_kmer["exp_freq"] = top_kmer["kmer"].apply(lambda x: calc_exp_freq(x, exp_freq_dict))
    
    # 
    top_kmer["enrichment_score"] = top_kmer["obs_freq"] / top_kmer["exp_freq"]

    # top_mk-mer
    top_kmer = top_kmer.sort_values(by="enrichment_score", ascending=False).head(top_m)

    # tsv
    top_kmer.to_csv(kmer_file.replace(".txt", f"_top{top_m}.tsv"), sep="\t", header=True, index=False)

# parse_args()
if __name__ == "__main__":

    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description="k-merk-mertop_mk-mer")
    parser.add_argument("kmer_file", type=str, help="kmer")
    parser.add_argument("total_obs_count", type=int, help="k-mer")
    parser.add_argument("exp_freq_dict_type", type=str, help="'grch38_p14''t2t'GRCh38_p14T2T")
    parser.add_argument("--top_m", type=int, default=10, help="top_mk-mer,10")

    args = parser.parse_args()

    calculate_enrichment_score(args.kmer_file, args.total_obs_count, args.exp_freq_dict_type, args.top_m)

import pandas as pd
import glob
from pathlib import Path
def kmer_dict(jf_txt_file,top_m):
    """
    Args:
        jf_txt_file (str): dump
        top_mintk-mertopk-mer
    
    Fun
        k-mertop Mk-merkeyk-mervaluek-mercountdicttsv
        pandas
          
    """
    kmer = pd.read_csv(jf_txt_file,sep=" ",header=None,names=["mer","count"])
    # top_m
    kmer = kmer.sort_values(by="count",ascending=False).head(top_m)
    
    # tsv
    kmer.to_csv(jf_txt_file.replace(".txt",f"_{top_m}.tsv"),sep="\t",header=True)
    
    # k-mer
    kmer_dict = dict(zip(kmer["mer"],kmer["count"]))
    return kmer_dict
    

# k-merkmer_dicttop Mk-mer
Q1_dir = "/data1/project/omics_final/Q1"
kmer_files = glob.glob(f"{Q1_dir}/*.txt")

kmer_results = {}
for each_kmer in kmer_files:
    each_kmer_name = Path(each_kmer).stem  # 
    print(f": {each_kmer_name}\n")
    
    # k-mer10k-mer
    # 
    
    kmer_results[each_kmer_name] = kmer_dict(each_kmer,top_m=10)
    print(f": kmer_results['{each_kmer_name}']\n")

#!/bin/bash
Q1_dir="/data1/project/omics_final/Q1"

for count in ${Q1_dir}/*.txt;do 

    prefix=$(basename ${count} .txt)
    
    sort -k2 -nr ${count} | head -n 10 > ${Q1_dir}/${prefix}_top10.txt  
     
done
